Here's the PlantUML component diagram for LectureLens focusing on the general architectural view:

```plantuml
@startuml takoko55_LectureLens

package "Frontend (React)" {
  [App.jsx] as App
  [SyllabusSearch.jsx] as Search
  [GlassCard.jsx] as Card
  [LecturePage.jsx] as Lecture
  [ReviewItem.jsx] as ReviewItem
  [Auth.jsx] as Auth
  [ReviewPost.jsx] as ReviewPost
  [useQueryReviews.jsx] as QueryHooks
  [useMutateReview.jsx] as MutationHooks
  [Zustand Store] as Store
}

package "Backend (Go)" {
  [main.go] as Main
  [router.go] as Router
  [controller] as Controller
  [usecase] as Usecase
  [repository] as Repository
  [model] as Model
  [db.go] as DB
  [migrate.go] as Migrate
}

database "PostgreSQL" as Postgres {
  [Users]
  [Lectures]
  [Reviews]
}

App --> Search
App --> Lecture
App --> Auth
Search --> Card
Lecture --> ReviewItem
Lecture --> ReviewPost
ReviewPost --> QueryHooks
ReviewPost --> MutationHooks
QueryHooks --> Store
MutationHooks --> Store

Router --> Controller
Controller --> Usecase
Usecase --> Repository
Repository --> Model
Model --> DB
DB --> Postgres
Migrate --> Postgres

Frontend -> Backend : REST API
Backend -> Postgres : SQL

@enduml
```